      <!--   Icon Section   -->
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col s12 m4">
          <div class="icon-block">
            <h2 class="center red-text"><i class="material-icons">store</i></h2>
            <h5 class="center">Rules</h5>

            <p class="light">
                You may choose only up to one fighter from the Sanyaku ranks (Ozeki, Komusubi, Sekiwake) and may choose six total fighters. You do not have to choose a Sanyaku but it is highly recommended since they earned their position by winning a lot.
                Substitutes may only be used if your fighter withdraws due to injury. You may not withdraw a fighter to use a substitute unless they are no longer active in the tournament.
                If you have rule suggestions or concerns please e-mail them to GYOJI@WPCTS.COM
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col s12 m4">
          <div class="icon-block">
            <h2 class="center red-text"><i class="material-icons">info</i></h2>
            <h5 class="center">Points</h5>
            <p class="light">
                Win: 1 Point<br>
                Loss by kimarite (penalty): -1 Point<br>
                Maegashira win against a Yokozuna: 3 Points<br>
                Win a technique trophy: 2 Points<br>
                Win the tournament: 5 Points<br>
                Gyoji (Referee) knocked down: 1 Point for both fighters<br>
                Gyoji suicide: 1000 Points for both fighters<br>

                Your substitute only gains points for the days they are active and you keep points your withdrawn fighter got until the point they withdraw from the tournament.
                <br>If your fighter withdraws from the tournament and is replaced they will not return to your active roster even if they return to the tournament.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col s12 m4">
          <div class="icon-block">
            <h2 class="center red-text"><i class="material-icons">local_dining</i></h2>
            <h5 class="center">Tournament Setup</h5>

            <p class="light">
                Tournament rosters lock the day before the tournament begins at midnight. All players are not required to pick six fighters but there is no benefit to leaving your roster unfilled.
                Any user who has submitted a roster of any kind before the deadline is eligible to win. Each tournament all users will also be competing against the <a href="/chodes">Chodes Team</a>.
                Any disputes or updates (penalty loss, overturned win, withdrawal abstained) that are missed by the site data should be reported to GYOJI@WPCTS.COM 
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

